I'll calculate the required financial ratios step by step.

## Step 1: Calculate Return on Equity (ROE)
ROE = Net Profit / Total Owner's Equity × 100%

Net Profit (from income statement) = $1,167,783.63
Total Owner's Equity (from end balance sheet) = $14,167,783.63

ROE = $1,167,783.63 / $14,167,783.63 × 100% = 0.0824 × 100% = 8.24%

## Step 2: Calculate Debt to Asset Ratio
Debt to Asset Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Assets

Total Liabilities (from end balance sheet) = $631,880.98
Total Assets (from end balance sheet) = $14,799,664.61

Debt to Asset Ratio = $631,880.98 / $14,799,664.61 = 0.0427 ≈ 0.04

## Step 3: Calculate Gross Profit Margin
Gross Profit Margin = Gross Profit / Total Revenue × 100%

Gross Profit (from income statement) = $2,060,619.40
Total Revenue (from income statement) = $3,397,619.40

Gross Profit Margin = $2,060,619.40 / $3,397,619.40 × 100% = 0.6065 × 100% = 60.65%
